@NODE INTRO "What the hell is this thing??"

ZYTES What is it ???

hehe a new word thats for shure another world first for MDR/Venom

nah its a nice looking bytes avail door run from MCI and shown after the
Download Ansi, saves having loads of crap TXT tagged on the ansi.
Why well i got pissed off trying to make DOWNLOADMSG.TXT look nice so all
i have to do now is look in my fav ansi collections cut the cool ansi out
colour it in and forget about appending shit loads of bullshit as ZYTES
looks really nice and makes me happy :) maybe u as well ?

Also in this Archive is a door called bytes, this is the same thing slightly
different output this is for your users so they can type BYTES and see whats
owing to them how many times have u seen em press D just to see what they
have, this may i repeat may stop them hehe as it will prob take em 12 months
to see that its there (bastards)

finally why have we included a D command? there is some strange problem in
/X if u run any command from MCI on the download screen, /X forgets the
command line (i.e. any files specified on that line) i first discovered this
when i installed NewRequest v1.o © fanta ^ Ice-T Therion/X-Design ^ Aquarius
Joe fix this please ;) all this does is cure the problem nothing else apart
from selecting your user.data for freedownload haha no only joking :)

Hope sysops find this usefull for other doors not just ours.
@ENDNODE
@NODE INSTALL "How to get it to go PLING!!"

Just append it to your DOWNLOADMSG.TXT, take a look at mine if u aint shure.

~08SR_BBS:SCREENS/CONF/DOWNLOADMSG|~CC_ZYTES|

Copy all icons to the same place they are in this archive
copy all doors to the same place as they are in this archive

There is an 030 compiled version, if u want to use this just change the
tooltypes in the icons.

OK thats it installed Please use my ZYTES.info and BYTES.info as if you
look inside them u will see the FUN part of this door is you the sysop can
change the remarks that come up ime not going to explain the remarks hehe
i think you will get the idea :))

** IMPORTANT ZYTES.INFO MUST GO IN SYSCMD OR IT WILL NOT WORK **
@ENDNODE
